\par \'93We should at least get samples of the acid off the lawn there,\'94 Martinho said. \'93And that hole will have to be investigated.\'94
\par \'93I\rquote ve sent for our Security Section,\'94 Chen-Lhu said. He turned away, thinking of how he would have to compose the reports on this\emdash the one for his superiors in the IEO and the special report for his own government.
\par \'93Did you see how it appeared to dissolve downward into the hole when I hit it with the spray?\'94 Martinho asked. \'93That poison can be painful, Travis. A man would\rquote ve screamed.\'94
\par \'93A man in protective clothing,\'94 Chen-Lhu, speaking without turning. But he began to wonder about Martinho. The man seemed genuinely puzzled. No matter. This whole incident was going to be useful. Chen-Lhu saw that now.
\par \'93But it came back out of the hole,\'94 Vierho said. \'93You saw that. It came back.\'94
\par An abrupt growling sound came from the people being pushed out of the Plaza. It passed through them like a wind\emdash voice to voice to voice.
\par Martinho turned, studied them. \'93Vierho,\'94 he said.
\par \'93Jefe?\'94
\par \'93Get blast-pellet carbines from the truck.\'94
\par \'93At once, Jefe.\'94
\par Vierho trotted across the lawn toward the truck which stood now in an open area with only a scattering of bandeirantes around it. Martinho recognized some of the men\emdash those of Alvarez seemed most
 numerous, but there were bandeirantes also of the Hermosillo and Junitza.
\par \'93What do you want with blast-pellet weapons?\'94 Chen-Lhu asked.
\par \'93I am going to look in that hole.\'94
\par \'93My Security men will be here soon. We\rquote ll wait for them.\'94
\par \'93I am going now.\'94
\par \'93Martinho, I\rquote m telling you that\'85\'94
\par \'93You are not the government of Brazil, Doctor. I am licensed by my government for a specific task. I am pledged to carry out that task wherever\'85\'94
\par \'93Martinho, if you destroy evidence of\'85\'94
\par \'93You were not out here facing those things, Doctor. You were safe back there at the Plaza\rquote s edge while I was earning the right to look in that hole.\'94
\par Chen-Lhu\rquote s face grew rigid with anger, but he held himself silent until he knew he could control his voice, then said, \'93In that case, I will go with you now.\'94
\par \'93As you wish.\'94
\par Martinho turned away, stared across the Plaza to where the carbines were being handed out of the rear of his truck. Vierho collected them, headed back across the lawn. A tall, bald-headed Negro with}{
