\par \'93There\rquote s Alvarez,\'94 Chen-Lhu said.
\par \'93I see him.\'94
\par Chen-Lhu faced Martinho, assumed a rueful smile to match his tone. \'93Johnny\emdash let us not fight. You know why the IEO assigned me to Brazil.\'94
\par \'93I know. China\rquote s already completed the realignment of its insects. You\rquote re a big success.\'94
\par \'93We\rquote ve nothing but the mutated bees now, Johnny\emdash not a single creature to spread disease or eat food intended for humans.\'94
\par \'93I know, Travis. And you\rquote re here to make our job easier.\'94
\par Chen-Lhu frowned at the tone of patient disbelief in Martinho\rquote s voice. He said, \'93Exactly.\'94
\par \'93Then why won\rquote t you let our observers or those from the U.N. go in and see for themselves, Doctor?\'94
\par \'93Johnny! You certainly must know how long my country suffered under the white imperialists. Some of our people believe the danger\rquote s still there. They see spies everywhere.\'94
\par \'93But you\rquote re more a man of the world, more understanding, eh, Travis?\'94
\par \'93Of course! My great grandmother was English, one of }{\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 the}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183  Travis-Huntingtons. 
