\par \'93It\rquote s a wonder your country trusts you,\'94 Martinho said. \'93You\rquote re part white imperialist.\'94 He turned to greet Alvarez as the Negro stopped in front of them. \'93Hi, Benito. Sorry about your arm.\'94
\par \'93Hullo, Johnny.\'94 Alvarez\rquote s voice was deep and rumbling. \'93God protected me. I will recover.\'94 He glanced down at the carbines in Vierho\rquote s hands, returned his attention to Martinho. \'93
I heard the Padre here asking for blast-pellets. You could only want them for one reason.\'94
\par \'93I have to look in that hole, Benito.\'94
\par Alvarez turned, gave a stiff little bow to Chen-Lhu. \'93And you have no objections, Doctor?\'94
\par \'93I\rquote ve objections, but no authority,\'94 Chen-Lhu said. \'93Is the arm severely injured? I will have my own physicians see to it.\'94
