\par \'93You will not disturb anything there?\'94 Chen-Lhu asked.
\par \'93We\rquote re as anxious as you to find out what that is,\'94 Alvarez said.
\par \'93Let\rquote s go,\'94 Martinho said.
\par Chen-Lhu trotted off to the right where an IEO field truck could be seen making its way through a side street. The crowd appeared to be giving trouble there, resisting efforts to expel them from the Plaza area.
\par Alvarez turned the control handle and the shield began crawling across the lawn.
\par In a low voice, Alvarez said, \'93Johnny, why doesn\rquote t the doctor suspect the Carsonites?\'94
\par \'93He has a spy system as good as anything in the world,\'94 Martinho said. \'93He must know.\'94 He kept his gaze on the disturbed patch of lawn ahead of them, that mysterious place beside the fountain.
\par \'93But what better way to sabotage us than to discredit the bandeirantes?\'94
\par \'93True, but I don\rquote t think Travis Huntington Chen-Lhu would make such a mistake.\'94 And he thought: }{\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 It is strange how that patch of lawn both attracts and repels}{
\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 .
\par \'93You and I have been rivals at the bid many times, Johnny. Perhaps we forget sometimes that we have a common enemy.\'94
\par \'93Do you name that enemy?\'94
\par \'93It\rquote s the enemy in the jungles, in the grass of the savannahs and under the ground. The Chinese took twenty-two years\'85\'94
\par \'93Do you suspect them?\'94 Martinho glanced at his companion, noting the glower of concentration of Alvarez\rquote s face. \'93They will not let us inspect their results.\'94
\par \'93The Chinese are paranoid. They leaned that way before they ever collided with the Western world and the Western world merely confirmed them in this sickness. Suspect the Chinese? I don\rquote t think so.\'94
\par \'93I do,\'94 Martinho said. \'93I suspect everyone.\'94
\par A feeling of gloom overtook him at the sound of his own words. It was true\emdash he suspected everyone, even Benito here, and Chen-Lhu\'85 and the lovely Rhin Kelly. He said, \'93
I think often of the ancient insecticides, how the insects grew ever stronger in spite of\emdash or because of\emdash the insect poisons.\'94
\par A sound behind them caught Martinho\rquote s attention. He put a hand on Alvarez\rquote s arm, stopped the shield, turned.
\par It was Vierho followed by a slave-cart piled with gear. Martinho identified a long pry bar there, a large body hood that must have been intended for Alvarez, packages of plastic explosive.
