\par \'93Jefe\'85 you are not going to use the shield?\'94
\par \'93There isn\rquote t time.\'94 He stepped around the shield before Vierho could answer. The beam of a handlight stabbed down at the ground ahead of him. He crouched, slid the tip of the prybar along the grass, digging, pushing. 
