\par More handlights glared onto the lawn ahead of him. Martinho looked up to see a ring of shields around them\emdash IEO and bandeirante uniforms.
\par Again he focused on the patch of lawn.
\par \'93Padre, I\rquote m going to pry it up. Be ready.\'94
\par \'93Of course, Jefe.\'94
\par Martinho put a foot under the bar as fulcrum, leaned on his end. The trapdoor lifted slowly. It appeared to be sealed with a gummy mixture that came up in trailing sheets. A whiff of sulphur and corrosive sublimate told Martinho what the sealant must be
