\par There\rquote d been a portable television for a while, but its range had been limited and now it no longer worked.
\par News ended and music blared from the speaker. The brain signaled for the instrument to be silenced. The brain lay there then in the welcome silence, thinking, pulsing.
\par It was a mass about four meters in diameter and half a meter deep, knowing itself as a \'93Supreme Integration,\'94 filled with passive alertness, yet always more than a little irritated by the necessities which kept it anchored to this cave sanctuary.

\par A mobile sensory mask which it could shift and flex at will\emdash forming now a disc, then a membranous funnel, and even the simulation of a giant human face\emdash lay like a cap across the brain\rquote 
