\par The moon-frosted jungle told him nothing.
\par The Goyaz: this was the region being saved for the final assault, using mobile barrier lines when the circle was short enough.
\par \'93How much farther?\'94 Joao asked.
\par \'93Soon.\'94
\par Joao armed the emergency charge that would separate the front and rear compartments of the truck when he fired it. The stub wings of the front pod and its emergency rocket motors would get him back into bandeirante country.
\par With the }{\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 specimen}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183  behind him safely subdued, Joao hoped.
\par He looked up through the canopy, scanned the horizon as far as he could. Was that moonlight glistening on a truck far back to the right? He couldn\rquote t be certain\'85 but it seemed to be.
\par \'93Soon?\'94 Joao asked.
\par \'93Ahead,\'94 the creature rasped.
\par The modulated stridulation beneath that voice sent a shiver along Joao\rquote s spine. Joao said, \'93My father\'85\'94
\par \'93Hospital for\'85 the father\'85 ahead,\'94 the creature said.
\par It would be dawn soon, Joao realized. He could see the first false line of light along the horizon behind. This night had passed so swiftly. Joao wondered if his guard had injected some time-distorting drug into him without his knowledge. 
