t time for fatigue or boredom when he had to record every landmark half-visible in the night, sense everything he could about these creatures around him. The bitter-clean smell of oxalic acid hinted at acid-to-oxygen chemistry.
\par But how did they coordinate all those separate insect units?
\par They appeared conscious. Was that more mimicry? What did they use for a brain?
\par Dawn came, revealing the plateau of the Mato Grosso: a caldron of liquid green boiling over the edge of the world. Joao looked out his side windows in time to see the truck\rquote 
s long shadow bounce across a clearing: stark galvanized metal roofs against the green\emdash a }{\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 sitiante}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 
 abandoned in the Resettlement, or perhaps the }{\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 barracao}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183  of a }{
\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 fazenda}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183  on the coffee frontier. It had be
en a likely place for a warehouse, standing as it had beside a small stream with the land around it bearing signs of riverbank agriculture.
\par Joao knew this region; he could put the bandeirante grid map over it in his imagination\emdash five degrees of latitude and six degrees of longitude it covered. Once it had been a place of isolated fazendas farmed by independent browns and blacks and }{
\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 branco sertanistos}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183  chained to the encomendero plantation system. 
The parents of Benito Alvarez had come from here. It was hardwood jungles, narrow rivers with banks overgrown by lush trees and ferns, savannahs and tangled life.
\par Here and there along the higher reaches of the rivers lay the remains of hydroelectric plants long since abandoned, like the one at Paulo Afonso Falls\emdash all replaced by sun power and atomics.
\par This was it: the }{\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 sertao}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183  of the Goyaz. 
Even in this age it remained primitive, a fact blamed on the insects and disease. It lay there, the last stronghold of teeming insect life in the Western Hemisphere, waiting for a modern tropical technology to lift it into the Twenty-first Century.
\par Supplies for the bandeirante assault would come by way of Sao Paulo, by air and by transport on the multi-decked highways, then on antique diesel trains to Itapira, by aviadores river runners
 to Bahus and by airtruck to Registo and Leopoldina on the Araguaya.
\par And when it was done\emdash the people would return, coming back from the Resettlement Plan areas and the metropolitan shantytowns.
\par A passage of turbulent air shook the truck, breaking Joao from his reverie, forcing him into an acute consciousness of his situation.
\par A glance at his guard showed the creature still crouched there, watchful\'85 as patient as the Indio it mimicked. The presence of the thing behind him had become cumulative, and Joao found himself required to combat a growing sense of revulsion.
\par The gleaming mechanical pragmatism of the truck pod around him felt as though it were at war with the insect creature. It had no business here in this cabin flying smoothly above the area where its kind ruled supreme.
\par Joao looked out and down at the green flow of forest, the }{\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 zona da mata}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 . 
