JOAO SAT up, clawed the jelly hood from his face, stared across the savannah. The grass there seethed and boiled with insects around an Irmandades airtruck.
\par A voice said, \'93Did you kill everything inside the pod?\'94
\par \'93Everything that moved.\'94 The reply was husky, halting, as though overcoming pain.
\par \'93Is there anything in it we can use?\'94
\par \'93The radio\rquote s destroyed.\'94
\par \'93Of course. That\rquote s the first thing they go for.\'94
\par Joao looked around him, counted seven of his Irmandades\emdash Vierho, Thome, Ramon, Pietr, Lon\'85
\par His eye was caught by the group clustered beyond his men\emdash Rhin Kelly among them. Her red hair was awry. Dirt streaked her face. There was a wild, glazed look in her green eyes. She was glaring at him.
\par He saw his pod then, to the right, on its side and just within what appeared to be a perimeter ditch. Foam and spray residue were all over it. His eye traversed the line of the ditch, saw that it ringed a hard
-packed dirt area with the tents in the center and savannah beyond. Two men in green IEO uniforms stood beside him holding sprayer handtanks.
\par Joao returned his attention to Rhin, remembering her as he\rquote d seen her in Bahia\rquote s }{\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 A\rquote Chigua}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 
. Now she wore a plain IEO field uniform, its green blotched by red-brown dirt. Her eyes held no invitation at all.
\par \'93I see poetic justice in this\emdash traitors,\'94 she said.
\par Her hysterical tone of voice caught Joao\rquote s ear and it took a second for her words to filter through. }{\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 Traitors?}{
\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 
\par He grew aware of the bedraggled, worn look of the IEO people.
\par Vierho approached, helped Joao to his feet, proffered a cloth to wipe off the jelly.
\par \'93Jefe, what is happening?\'94 Vierho asked. \'93We picked up your signal, but you didn\rquote t answer.\'94
\par \'93Later,\'94 Joao rasped as he recognized the anger in Rhin and her companions. Rhin appeared feverish and ill.
\par Hands brushed Joao, clearing dead insects off him. The pain from the stings and bites receded under the medicant neutralizer.
\par \'93Whose skeleton is that in your pod?\'94 one of the IEO people asked.
\par Before Joao could answer, Rhin said, \'93Death and skeletons should be nothing new for Joao Martinho, }{\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 traitor}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 
 of the Piratininga!\'94
\par \'93They are crazy, that is the only thing, I think,\'94 Vierho said.
\par \'93Your pets turned on you, didn\rquote t they?\'94 Rhin demanded. \'93The skeleton, that\rquote s all that\rquote s left of one of you, eh?\'94
\par \'93What is this talk of skeletons?\'94 Vierho asked.
\par \'93Your jefe knows,\'94 Rhin said.
\par \'93Would you be so kind as to explain?\'94 Joao asked.
\par \'93I don\rquote t need to explain,\'94 she said. \'93Let your friends out there explain.\'94 She pointed toward the rim of jungle beyond the savannah.
\par Joao looked there, saw a line of men in bandeirante white standing untouched amidst the leaping, boiling insects in the jungle shadow. He took a pair of binoculars from around the neck of one of his men, focused on the figures.
\par Knowing what to look for made the identification easy.
\par \'93Padre,\'94 Joao said.
\par Vierho bent close, rubbing at an insect sting beneath the acid scar on his cheek.
\par In a low voice, Joao explained about the figures at the jungle edge, handed over the glasses so that Vierho could see for himself the fine lines in the skin, the facet-glitter of the eyes.
\par \'93}{\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 Aiee}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 ,\'94 Vierho said.
\par \'93Do you recognize your friends?\'94 Rhin demanded.
\par Joao ignored her.
\par Vierho passed along the glasses with an explanation to another of the Irmandades. The two IEO men who had sprayed Joao came close, listening, turned their attention to the figures in the jungle shadows.
\par One of the IEO men crossed himself.
\par \'93That perimeter ditch,\'94 Joao said. \'93What\rquote s in it?\'94
\par \'93Couroq jelly,\'94 said the IEO man who\rquote d crossed himself. \'93It\rquote s all we had left for an insect barrier.\'94
\par \'93That won\rquote t stop them,\'94 Joao said.
\par \'93But it }{\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 has}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183  stopped them,\'94 the man said.
\par Joao nodded. He was having unpleasant suspicions about their position here. He looked at Rhin. \'93Dr. Kelly, where are the rest of your people?\'94 Joao passed his gaze around the IEO personnel, counting. \'93Surely there\rquote 
re more than six in an IEO field crew.\'94
\par Her lips compressed, but she remained silent.
\par The more Joao looked at her, the more ill she appeared.
\par \'93So?\'94 Joao said. He glanced around at the tents, seeing their weathered condition. \'93And where is your equipment, your trucks, lab hut, jitneys?\'94
\par \'93Funny thing you should ask,\'94 she said, but there was uncertainty in the sneering quality of her voice\emdash and that definite hysterical undertone. \'93About a kilometer into the trees over there\'94\emdash she nodded to her left\emdash \'93
is a wrecked jungle truck containing most of our\'85 equipment, as you call it. The track spools of our truck were eaten away by acid before we knew anything was wrong. The lift rotors were destroyed the same way\emdash everything.\'94
\par \'93Acid?\'94
\par \'93It smelled like oxalic, but acted more like hydrochloric,\'94 said one of her companions, a blond Nordic with a recent acid burn beneath his right eye.
\par \'93Start from the beginning,\'94 Joao said.
\par \'93We were cut off here\'85\'94 He broke off, glanced around.
\par \'93Eight days ago,\'94 Rhin said.
