\par \'93Our second night here we dug a well in one of the tents,\'94 she said. \'93River seepage, naturally. Water\rquote s loaded with poisons, some of them ours. That\rquote s what Vierho tasted: the bitterness. But my tests shows there\rquote 
s something else in that water: a hallucinogenic that produces a reaction very like schizophrenia. It isn\rquote t anything humans put there.\'94
\par Joao could feel energy pumping into him from the pack on his leg. A cramp like acute hunger knotted his stomach. When it passed, he said, \'93Something from\'85 }{\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 them}{
\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 .\'94
\par \'93Very likely,\'94 she said. \'93We\rquote ve rigged a crude still. There\rquote s a variable resistance to this hallucinogenic. Hogar appears to be completely immune, but he didn\rquote t get any of the venom drug. }{
\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 That}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183  seems to leave you wide open.\'94 Again she checked his pulse. \'93Are you feeling stronger?\'94
\par \'93Yes.\'94
\par The cramps were in the muscles of his thighs now\emdash rhythmic and painful. They receded.
\par \'93We\rquote ve analyzed that skeleton in your pod,\'94 she said. \'93An amazing thing. Remarkably like a human skeleton except for ridges and tiny holes\emdash presumably where the insects attach themselves and articulate it. It\rquote 
s bird-light but very strong. The kinship to chitin is quite apparent.\'94
\par Joao thought about this, letting the energy from the pack on his leg accumulate. He was feeling stronger by the second. So much seemed to have happened, though: the pod repaired, that skeleton analyzed.
\par \'93How long have I been here?\'94 he asked.
\par \'93Four days,\'94 she said. She glanced at her wristwatch. \'93Almost to the hour. It\rquote s still fairly early.\'94
\par Joao grew aware then of the forced cheerfulness in her tone. What was she hiding? Before he could explore the question, a hiss of fabric and brief flash of sunlight told of someone entering the tent.
\par Chen-Lhu appeared behind Rhin. The Chinese seemed to have aged fifty years since Joao had last seen him. Skin sagged and wrinkled at his jawline. The cheeks were concave pockets. He walked with a fragile caution.
\par \'93I see the patient is awake,\'94 he said.
\par The voice surprised Joao by its strength\emdash as though all the man\rquote s physical energy had been channeled into this one aspect of him.
\par \'93He\rquote s under pack right now,\'94 she said.
\par \'93Wise,\'94 Chen-Lhu said. \'93There isn\rquote t much time. Have you told him?\'94
\par \'93Only that we\rquote ve repaired his truck pod.\'94
\par }{\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 This must be phrased very delicately}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 , Chen-Lhu thought. }{
\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 Very delicately. Latin honor can shoot off at strange tangents.}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 
\par \'93We are going to attempt escaping in your pod,\'94 Chen-Lhu said.
\par \'93How can we?\'94 Joao asked. \'93That pod won\rquote t lift more than three people at the most.\'94
\par \'93Three people is all it\rquote ll carry, that is correct,\'94 Chen-Lhu said. \'93But it won\rquote t be required to lift them; in fact, it cannot lift them.\'94
\par \'93What do you mean?\'94
\par \'93Your landing was rather rough: one of your float-skids is damaged and you ruptured the belly tank. Most of the fuel was gone before we discovered the damage. There\rquote s also the matter of controls: they\rquote 
re not of the best, even after the Padre\rquote s most ingenious ministrations.\'94
\par \'93That still means only three people in it,\'94 Joao said.
\par \'93If we can\rquote t transmit a message, we can carry it,\'94 Rhin said.
\par }{\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 Good girl}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 , Chen-Lhu thought. He waited for Joao to absorb this.
\par \'93Who?\'94 Joao asked.
\par \'93Myself,\'94 Chen-Lhu said. \'93Only for the reason that I can testify to the debacle in my nation, warn your people before it\rquote s too late.\'94
\par Chen-Lhu\rquote s words brought an entire conversation flooding back into Joao\rquote s awareness\emdash in the tent: Hogar, Vierho\'85 Chen-Lhu babbling about\'85 about\'85
\par \'93Barren earth,\'94 Joao said.
\par \'93Your people must learn before it\rquote s too late,\'94 Chen-Lhu said. \'93So I will be one of the passengers. And Rhin here because\'85\'94 He managed a weak shrug. \'93\'85because of chivalry, I would say, but also because she\rquote s resourceful.
\'94
\par \'93That\rquote s two,\'94 Joao said.
\par \'93And you will make three,\'94 Chen-Lhu said, and he waited for the outburst.
\par But Joao merely said, \'93That doesn\rquote t make sense.\'94 He lifted his head, stared down along the length of his body on the cot. \'93Four days here and\'85\'94
\par \'93But you\rquote re the one with }{\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 pistolao}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 \emdash political connections,\'94 Rhin said. \'93
You can make people listen.\'94
\par Joao dropped his head back onto the cot.
\par \'93My own father wouldn\rquote t even listen to me!\'94
\par The statement evoked a surprising silence. Rhin looked up at Chen-Lhu, back to Joao.
\par \'93You have your own political pipelines, Travis,\'94 Joao said. \'93Probably better than mine.\'94
\par \'93And perhaps not,\'94 Chen-Lhu said. \'93Besides, you\rquote re the one who saw this creature close up, the one whose skeleton we will take back with us. You are the eye-witness.\'94
\par \'93We\rquote re all eye-witnesses.\'94
\par \'93It was put to a vote,\'94 Rhin said. \'93Your men insist.\'94
\par Joao looked from Rhin to Chen-Lhu, back to Rhin. \'93That still leaves twelve men here. What happens to them?\'94
\par \'93Only eight now,\'94 Rhin whispered.
\par \'93Who?\'94 Joao managed.
\par \'93Hogar,\'94 she said. \'93Thome of your crew; two of my field aides: Cardin and Lewis.\'94
\par \'93How?\'94
\par \'93There is a thing that looks like a }{\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 qena}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183  flute,\'94 Chen-Lhu said. \'93
The creature in your truck pod carried one.\'94
\par \'93Dart gun,\'94 Joao said.
\par \'93No,\'94 Chen-Lhu said. \'93They mimic us better than that. It\rquote s a generator of a sonic-disruption pattern. What it disrupts is human red blood cells. They must get fairly close with it, though, and we\rquote 
ve been keeping them back since we discovered it.\'94
\par \'93You can see we have to get this information out,\'94 Rhin said.
\par }{\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 No doubt of that}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 , Joao thought.
\par \'93Surely there must be someone stronger, better able to insure the success of this,\'94 Joao said.
\par \'93You\rquote ll be as strong as any of us in a couple of hours,\'94 Rhin said. \'93We are not in the best condition, none of us.\'94
\par Joao stared up at the gray light of the tent ceiling. }{\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 Very little rocket fuel, damaged controls. They mean to make for the river, of course: float out in the pod. It\rquote 
ll afford some protection from those\'85 things.}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 
\par Rhin stood up. \'93You rest and build up your strength,\'94 she said. \'93I\rquote ll bring you some food in a little while. We have nothing but field rations, but at least they\rquote re loaded with energy.\'94
\par }{\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 What river is that?}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183  Joao wondered. }{\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 
The Itapura, very likely}{\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 . He made a rough estimate based on his knowledge of the region and the length of his flight over it before the crash landing here. }{
\i\cf1\lang1033\langfe1049\langnp1033\insrsid15279183\charrsid15279183 It\rquote ll be seven or eight hundred kilometers by river! And we\rquote re right on top of the rainy season. }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 We don\rquote t stand a chance!}{
