\par \'93Every creature I see out there, I have to ask myself: Is that really what it seems?\'94 Rhin said.
\par \'93Those are really monkeys,\'94 Joao said. \'93I think there are some things our friends cannot imitate.\'94
\par The river straightened now, and the hills pressed closer. Thick twistings of hardwood trees along both shores gave way to lines of sago palms backed by rising waves of the jungle\rquote s omnip
resent greens. Only infrequently was the green broken by smooth red-skinned trunks of }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 guayavilla}{\cf1\insrsid15279183  leaning over the water.
\par Around another bend, and they surprised a long-legged pink bird feeding in the shallows. It lifted on heavy pinions, flew downstream.
\par \'93Fasten your seatbelts,\'94 Joao said.
\par \'93Are you that certain?\'94 Chen-Lhu asked.
\par \'93Yes.\'94
\par Joao heard buckles snapping, fastened his own harness, looked at the dash to review Vierho\rquote s changes in controls. Igniter\'85 firing light\'85 throttle. He moved the wheel; how slu
ggish it felt. One silent prayer for the patch on the right hand float, and he set himself in readiness.
\par The sound came as a faint roaring like wind through trees. They felt another quickening of the current that swept the pod around a wide bend, turning i
n an eddy until it faced directly downstream, and there, no more than a kilometer away, they saw the snarled boiling of white water. Foam and misting spume hurled itself into the air. The sound was a crashing drum roar growing louder by the second.
\par Joao weighed the circumstances\emdash high walls of trees on both sides, narrowing channel, high black walls of wet rock on both sides of the rapids. There was only one way to go: through it.
\par Current and distance required careful judgment: the pod\rquote s floats had to hit the crosscurrent waves above the rapids at just the right moment for those waves to help break the river\rquote s grip on the floats.
\par }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 This\rquote ll be the place}{\cf1\insrsid15279183 , Chen-Lhu thought. }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 Our friends\rquote ll be here\'85 waiting for us}{\cf1\insrsid15279183 . He gripped a sprayrifle, tried to see both shores at once.

\par Rhin gripped the sides of her seat, pressed herself backward against the cushions. She felt that they were hurtling without hope toward the maelstrom.
\par \'93Something in the trees on our right,\'94 Chen-Lhu said. \'93Something overhead.\'94
\par A shadow darkened the water all around them. Fluttering white shapes began to obscure the view ahead.
\par Joao punched the igniter, counted\emdash one, two, three. Light off\emdash throttle.
\par The motors caught with a great banging, spitting roar that drowned the sound of the rapids. The pod surg
ed through the screen of insects, out of the shadow. Joao swerved them to avoid a line of foaming rocks in the upper pool. He nursed the throttle by the feeling of G-pressure against his back.
\par }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 Don\rquote t blow, baby}{\cf1\insrsid15279183 , he prayed. }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 Don\rquote t blow}{\cf1\insrsid15279183 .
\par \'93A net!\'94 Rhin screamed. \'93They have a net across the river!\'94
\par It lifted from the water above the rapids like a dripping snake.
\par Reflex moved Joao\rquote s hand on the throttle, sent the knob slamming against the dash.
\par The pod leaped, skimmed across a glossy pool. Slithering current tugged them sideways toward smooth black walls of rock. The net stood out directly ahead when the pod lifted, floats breaking from the water.
\par Up\'85 up.
\par Joao could see the river plunge off beyond the net, water leaping in crazy violence there as though trying to escape the glassy black walls of rock.
\par Something slapped the floats with a screech and sound of tearing. The pod\rquote s nose dipped, bounced up as Joao hauled on the wheel. A staccato rattling shook the craft. Spray filled the air all around.
\par In one flickering moment, Joao saw motion along the chasm\rquote s rim. A line of boulders thundered down there, fell behind.
\par Then they were out of it, airborne and climbing\emdash lurching, twisting\'85 but climbing. Joao eased the throttle back.
\par The pod thundered over a line of trees, back across the river. Another tree-spiked hill hot beneath them. A long straight avenue of water opened up ahead of them like turbulent brown grease.
\par Joao grew conscious of Rhin\rquote s voice: \'93Look at us go! Look at us go!\'94
\par \'93That was inspired flying,\'94 Chen-Lhu said.
\par Joao tried to swallow in a dry throat. The controls felt heavy under his hands. He saw downstream a great bend in the river, and beyond that a wide island-broken lake of flooded land.
\par }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 Brown river\'85 flooded land}{\cf1\insrsid15279183 , he thought.
\par He fishtailed the pod, shot a look back to the west. Brown clouds were piled there, with black beneath them: thunderheads! }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 Rain in the hills behind us}{\cf1\insrsid15279183 , he thought. }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 
Flood here. It must\rquote ve happened during the night}{\cf1\insrsid15279183 .
\par And he cursed himself for not noticing the change in water color earlier.
\par \'93What\rquote s wrong, Johnny?\'94 Chen-Lhu asked.
\par \'93Nothing we can do anything about.\'94
\par Joao eased the throttle back another notch, another. The motors sputtered, died. He shut off all fuel.
\par Wind whistled around them as Joao eased back on the wheel, trying to gain as much distance as possible. The pod began to stagger at the edge of stalling. He tipped the nose down, still nursing it for distance. But the pod flew like all pods\emdash 
