\par Joao looked up to his left at clouds hovering low above the trees. \'93And if there ever were going to be searchers, they sure as hell couldn\rquote t see us now.\'94
\par Rhin wet her lips with her tongue. She felt suddenly emptied of emotion, realized then how much she had counted on being found. \'93How\'85 how long does the rain last?\'94 she asked.
\par \'93Four or five months,\'94 Joao said.
\par An eddy turned the pod. Shoreline twisted across Joao\rquote s vision: greenery dimmed to pastel by the torrent. \'93Anybody been outside?\'94 he asked.
\par \'93I have,\'94 Chen-Lhu said.
\par Joao turned, saw dark patches of wetness on the IEO fatigues.
\par \'93Nothing out there except rain,\'94 Chen-Lhu said.
\par Joao\rquote s right leg began to itch. He reached down, was surprised to find the energy pack gone.
\par \'93You began showing muscle spasms during the night,\'94 Rhin said. \'93I took it off.\'94
\par \'93I must\rquote ve really been asleep.\'94 He touched her hand. \'93Thanks, nurse.\'94
\par She pulled her hand away.
\par Joao looked up, puzzled, but she turned, stared out her window.
\par \'93I\rquote m\'85 going outside,\'94 Joao said.
\par \'93Do you feel strong enough?\'94 she asked. \'93You were pretty weak.\'94
\par \'93I\rquote m all right.\'94
\par He stood up, made his way back to the hatch and down to the pontoon. The rain felt warm and fresh against his face. He stood on the end of the float, enjoying the freshness.
\par In the cabin, Chen-Lhu said, \'93Why didn\rquote t you go out and hold his hand, Rhin?\'94
\par \'93You\rquote re an utter bastard, Travis,\'94 she said.
\par \'93Do you love him a little?\'94
\par She turned, glared at him. \'93What do you want from me?\'94
\par \'93Your cooperation, my dear.\'94
\par \'93In what?\'94
\par \'93How would you like to have an emerald mine all your very own? Or perhaps diamonds? More wealth than you could possibly imagine?\'94
\par \'93In payment for what?\'94
\par \'93When the moment comes, Rhin, you\rquote ll know what to do. And meanwhile, you make a pliant blob of putty out of our bandeirante.\'94
\par She silenced an angry outburst, whirled away. And she thought: }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 Our bodies betray us. The Chen-Lhus of the world come along, push buttons, bend us and twist us\'85 I won\rquote t do it! I won\rquote 
