\par }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 I could kill her now and push Johnny off the float}{\cf1\insrsid15279183 , Chen-Lhu thought. }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 But this is a difficult craft to manage\'85 and I\rquote m not experienced in such matters}{
\cf1\insrsid15279183 .
\par Rhin turned a molten look on him.
\par }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 Perhaps she\rquote ll come around}{\cf1\insrsid15279183 , Chen-Lhu thought. }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 I know her weaknesses, certainly\emdash but I must be sure}{\cf1\insrsid15279183 .
\par Joao returned, slipped into his seat. He brought a fresh smell of wetness into the cabin, but the odor of mildew remained and it was growing stronger.
\par As the morning wore on, the rain slackened. A warm, misty feeling permeated the cabin\rquote s air. Clouds of gun-metal cotton lifted to brush the hilltops above the river and a beaded drapery of raindrops hung on every visible tree.
\par The pod bobbed and twisted along a swift mud-brown flow accompanied by more and more flotsam\emdash trees, brush, root islands as large as the pod, whole floes of grass and reeds.
\par Joao drowsed, wondering at the change in Rhin. In their world of the casual liaison, he knew he should merely shrug and make some witty remark. But he didn\rquote t feel casual or witty about Rhin. She had touched some chord in him that the pleasures o
f flesh had never before reached.
\par }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 Love?}{\cf1\insrsid15279183  he wondered.
\par But their world had fallen out of the notion of romantic love. There was only family and honor where those things counted and all else involved doing-the-right-thing, which usually meant salvaging the le
ast messy aspects from any situation that happened to fall apart.
\par No clear way of approaching his problem presented itself. Joao knew only that he was being nudged and pushed from within, that physical weakness contributed to the fuzziness of his thinking\'85 and besides, their whole situation was hopeless.
\par }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 I\rquote m sick}{\cf1\insrsid15279183 , he thought. }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 The whole world\rquote s sick}{\cf1\insrsid15279183 .
\par }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 In more ways than one}{\cf1\insrsid15279183 .
\par A buzzing sound invaded Joao\rquote s torpor. He snapped upright, wide awake.
\par \'93What\rquote s wrong?\'94 Rhin asked.
\par \'93Be quiet.\'94 He held up a hand to silence her, cocked his head to one side.
\par Chen-Lhu leaned forward over the back of Joao\rquote s seat. \'93A truck?\'94
\par \'93Yes, by God!\'94 Joao said. \'93And it\rquote s low.\'94 He glanced at the sky around them, started to release the canopy, was restrained by Chen-Lhu, who put a hand on his arm.
\par \'93Johnny, look there,\'94 Chen-Lhu said. He pointed to the left.
\par Joao turned.
\par From the shore came what appeared at first to be an odd cloud\emdash wide, thick, moving with a purposeful directness. The cloud resolved itself into a mob of fluttering white, gra
y and gold insects. They came in at about fifty meters above the pod and the water darkened with their shadow.
\par The shadow reached out all around the pod and paced it, a moving cover to hide them from anything in the sky.
\par As the import of the maneuver penetrated Joao\rquote s awareness, he turned, stared at Chen-Lhu. The man\rquote s face appeared gray with shock.
\par \'93That\rquote s\'85 deliberate,\'94 Rhin whispered.
\par \'93How can it be?\'94 Chen-Lhu asked. \'93How can it be? How can it be?\'94
\par In the same moment, Chen-Lhu saw how Joao studied him, realized his own emotions. Anger at himself filled Chen-Lhu. }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 I must not show fear to these savages!}{\cf1\insrsid15279183 
 he thought. He forced himself to sit back, to smile and shake his head.
\par \'93To train insects,\'94 Chen-Lhu said. \'93It is almost unbelievable\'85 but someone obviously has done it. We see the evidence.\'94
\par \'93Please, God,\'94 Rhin whispered. \'93Please.\'94
\par \'93Oh, stop your silly prattle, woman,\'94 Chen-Lhu said. And even as he spoke, he knew that was the wrong tack to take with Rhin, and he said, \'93You must remain calm, Rhin. Hysterics serve no purpose.\'94
