\par \'93We don\rquote t want to hear about your damned orgy!\'94 Rhin snapped.
\par }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 The flesh}{\cf1\insrsid15279183 , Chen-Lhu thought. }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 She dares not listen to anything that reminds her of her own flesh. That is her weakness, for sure. It is good that I know this.}{\cf1\insrsid15279183 

\par \'93So?\'94 Chen-Lhu said. \'93Very well. Tell us then about the fine life in Dublin, my dear Rhin. I love to hear of the people who trade wives and mistresses and ride horses and pretend the past has never died.\'94
\par \'93You\rquote re really a terrible man,\'94 Rhin said.
\par \'93Excellent!\'94 Chen-Lhu said. \'93You may hate me, Rhin; I permit it. Hate keeps one occupied, too. One may indulge hate while one thinks about such things as wealth and pleasures. There are times when hate is a much mo
re profitable occupation than making love.\'94
\par Joao turned, studied Chen-Lhu, hearing the words, seeing the harsh control on the man\rquote s face. }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 He uses words as weapons}{\cf1\insrsid15279183 , Joao thought. }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 
