\par Joao slipped into his seat.
\par The pod danced across a pattern of eddy ripples, turned and faced downstream toward a shaft of sunlight that stabbed through the clouds. Slowly, great patches of blue opened in the clouds.
\par \'93There\rquote s the sun, the good old sun,\'94 Rhin said, \'93now that we don\rquote t need it.\'94
\par A need for male protection came over Rhin, and she leaned her head against Joao\rquote s shoulder. \'93It\rquote s going to be sticky hot,\'94 she whispered.
\par \'93If you\rquote d like to be alone, I could step out on the float,\'94 Chen-Lhu mocked.
\par \'93Ignore the bastard,\'94 Rhin said.
\par }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 Do I dare ignore him?}{\cf1\insrsid15279183  Joao wondered. }{\i\cf1\insrsid15279183 Is that her purpose\emdash to make me ignore him? Do I dare?}{\cf1\insrsid15279183 
